{
  "article_id": "TheTidings1904_Sep30",
  "paragraphs": [
    [
      {
        "text": "The bereft mother",
        "tropes": [
          3
        ],
        "entity_key": "lw",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "evinced the greatest fondness for Mrs. Nidiver's children, caressing and playing with them by the hour, and telling",
        "tropes": [
          3
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "the lady",
        "tropes": [
          3
        ],
        "entity_key": "sni",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": ", by signs, that when she swam back to the shore",
        "tropes": [
          3
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "her baby",
        "tropes": [
          3
        ],
        "entity_key": "lwchild",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "was gone, and she believed the dogs had eaten it. She went over, again and again, her grief at its loss; her frantic search for it, even after it had been gone a long time; her dread of being alone; her hope, for years, of rescue, and at last the despair that in time became resignation.",
        "tropes": [
          3
        ]
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "The visitors sometimes gave her presents, which she put aside until the donors had departed, seeming to know by intuition that they would be offended if she refused to accept them; but as soon as the guests were gone she called the little children, and distributed her gifts among them, laughing if they were pleased, and happy in their joy.",
        "tropes": [
          3
        ]
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "A few days after her arrival,"
      },
      {
        "text": "Father Antonio Jimeno",
        "entity_key": "aji",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "sent for Indians from the missions of"
      },
      {
        "text": "San Fernando",
        "entity_key": "mi_sfern",
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": "and"
      },
      {
        "text": "Santa Ynez",
        "entity_key": "mi_sy",
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": ", in hope of finding some one who could converse with"
      },
      {
        "text": "the islander",
        "entity_key": "lw",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": ". At that time there were"
      },
      {
        "text": "Indians",
        "entity_key": "natam_pepimaros",
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": "living in"
      },
      {
        "text": "Los Angeles county",
        "entity_key": "co_la",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", belonging to the"
      },
      {
        "text": "Pepimaros",
        "entity_key": "natam_pepimaros",
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": ", who, it was said, had in former years communication with"
      },
      {
        "text": "the San Nicolas Indians",
        "entity_key": "natam_NicolenoTongva",
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": ". But neither these, nor those from"
      },
      {
        "text": "San Buena Ventura",
        "entity_key": "ci_ven",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", or"
      },
      {
        "text": "Santa Barbara",
        "entity_key": "ci_sb",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", could understand her, or make themselves understood."
      },
      {
        "text": "In less than two decades after",
        "tropes": [
          6
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "the little band",
        "tropes": [
          6
        ],
        "entity_key": "bhagroup",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "had left",
        "tropes": [
          6
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "San Nicolas",
        "tropes": [
          6
        ],
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", their whereabouts could not be discovered. They were a mere drop in the stream of serfs known by the general name of",
        "tropes": [
          6
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "Mission Indians",
        "tropes": [
          6
        ],
        "entity_key": "natam_missionindians",
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": ".",
        "tropes": [
          6
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "Beyond a few words, nothing was ever known of her tongue. A hide she called to-co (to-kay); a man, nache (nah-chey); the sky, te-gua (tay-gwah); the body, pinche (pin-oo-chey). She learned a few Spanish words: pan (bread), papas (potatoes), caballo (horse). Sometimes she called Captain Nidiver, in Spanish, tata (father), sometimes nana (mother)."
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "The gentleness, modesty and tact of",
        "tropes": [
          3
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "the untutored wild woman of the Pacific",
        "tropes": [
          3
        ],
        "entity_key": "lw",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "were so foreign to ideas of the savage nature, that some parties believed that she was not an Indian, but a person of distinction cast away by shipwreck, and adopted by",
        "tropes": [
          3
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "the islanders",
        "tropes": [
          3
        ],
        "entity_key": "bhagroup",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "before their removal from",
        "tropes": [
          3
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "their home",
        "tropes": [
          3
        ],
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ". Others were certain, from her evident refinement, that she had not been long alone, but had drifted to",
        "tropes": [
          3
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "San Nicolas",
        "tropes": [
          3
        ],
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "after",
        "tropes": [
          3
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "the Indian woman",
        "tropes": [
          3
        ],
        "entity_key": "lw",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "perished in the surf, and had by mistake been taken for",
        "tropes": [
          3
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "the original savage",
        "tropes": [
          3
        ],
        "entity_key": "lw",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": ". [T]he",
        "tropes": [
          3
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "old sailors who rescued her",
        "tropes": [
          3
        ],
        "entity_keys": [
          "gni",
          "cdi",
          "col",
          "cook",
          "msh",
          "poli",
          "nsk",
          "hva"
        ],
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "affirm that she was an Indian, the same who jumped from",
        "tropes": [
          3
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "the schooner",
        "tropes": [
          3
        ],
        "entity_key": "sh_peoresnada",
        "entity_type": "ship"
      },
      {
        "text": "to save",
        "tropes": [
          3
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "her child",
        "tropes": [
          3
        ],
        "entity_key": "lwchild",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": ".",
        "tropes": [
          3
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "The representative of a lost tribe",
        "tropes": [
          3
        ],
        "entity_key": "lw",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": ", she stands out from the Indians of the coast, the possessor of noble and distinctive traits; provident, cleanly, tasteful, amiable, imitative, considerate, and with a maternal devotion which civilization has never surpassed.",
        "tropes": [
          3
        ]
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "She was greatly disappointed when none of"
      },
      {
        "text": "her kindred",
        "entity_key": "bhagroup",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "were found."
      },
      {
        "text": "She drooped under civilization; she missed the out door life of",
        "tropes": [
          3,
          6
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "her island camp",
        "tropes": [
          3,
          6
        ],
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ". After a few weeks she became too weak to walk; she was carried on to the porch every day in a chair.",
        "tropes": [
          3,
          6
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "She dozed in the sunshine, while the children played around her. She was patient and cheerful, looking eagerly into every new face for recognition, and sometimes singing softly to herself."
      },
      {
        "text": "Mrs. Nidiver",
        "entity_key": "sni",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "hoped a return to her old diet would help her. She procured seal's meat, and roasted it in ashes. When"
      },
      {
        "text": "the sick woman",
        "entity_key": "lw",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "saw it, she patted the nurse's hands affectionately, but could not eat the food. She fell from her chair one morning, and remained insensible for hours. Seeing the approach of death,"
      },
      {
        "text": "Mrs. Nidiver",
        "entity_key": "sni",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "sent for"
      },
      {
        "text": "a priest",
        "entity_key": "sanchez",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "to baptize"
      },
      {
        "text": "her protege",
        "entity_key": "lw",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": ". At first he refused, not knowing but that she had been baptized previously, although the burden of proof was against it. At length, heeding"
      },
      {
        "text": "the kind Catholic lady's distress",
        "entity_key": "sni",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": ", he consented to administer the rite, conditionally. As she was breathing her last, the sign of the cross was pressed on her cold brow, and"
      },
      {
        "text": "the unknown and nameless creature",
        "entity_key": "lw",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "was christened by"
      },
      {
        "text": "Father Sanchez",
        "entity_key": "sanchez",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": ", in the beautiful Spanish, \""
      },
      {
        "text": "Juana Marie",
        "entity_key": "lw",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": ".\" In a walled cemetery, from whose portals gleam ghastly skull and cross-bones, close to"
      },
      {
        "text": "the Santa Barbara Mission",
        "entity_key": "mi_sb",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", under the shelter of the tower is the neglected grave of a devoted mother,"
      },
      {
        "text": "the heroine of San Nicolas",
        "entity_key": "lw",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "."
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "The abandonment of"
      },
      {
        "text": "San Nicolas",
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "occurred forty-six years ago."
      },
      {
        "text": "The survivor of eighteen years' solitary captivity",
        "entity_key": "lw",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "arrived in"
      },
      {
        "text": "Santa Barbara",
        "entity_key": "ci_sb",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "the 8th of September, 1853."
      },
      {
        "text": "Captain Nidiver's house",
        "entity_key": "nideverhouse",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", where the stranger died, stands in sight of the ocean, and can be pointed out by any school boy in"
      },
      {
        "text": "the town",
        "entity_key": "ci_sb",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "."
      },
      {
        "text": "Nidiver",
        "entity_key": "gni",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "and"
      },
      {
        "text": "his wife",
        "entity_key": "sni",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "are living, and"
      },
      {
        "text": "their son George",
        "entity_key": "gnijr",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "follows the sea, as"
      },
      {
        "text": "his father",
        "entity_key": "gni",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "did before him."
      },
      {
        "text": "Carl Detman",
        "entity_key": "cdi",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": ", or"
      },
      {
        "text": "Charlie Brown",
        "entity_key": "cdi",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": ", as he is called by old sailors, may be found any day where the retired boatmen congregate."
      },
      {
        "text": "Thomas Jeffries",
        "entity_key": "tje",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "walks the streets in blouse, wide hat, and flowing hair."
      },
      {
        "text": "Dr. Brinkerhoff",
        "entity_key": "bri",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": ", who attended"
      },
      {
        "text": "the woman of San Nicolas",
        "entity_key": "lw",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": ", is a well known physician of"
      },
      {
        "text": "the city",
        "entity_key": "ci_sb",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "."
      },
      {
        "text": "Father Gonzales",
        "entity_key": "jru",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "died a few years ago, after a continuous residence of more than a quarter of a century in"
      },
      {
        "text": "the Mission",
        "entity_key": "mi_santabarbaramission",
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": ". For a long time he was partially paralyzed, and was carried about in a chair. I remember him as a little dark man, with eyes that blazed unnaturally from sunken sockets, his appearance rendered more startling by a white turban bound around his head. He is buried under the floor of"
      },
      {
        "text": "the old chapel",
        "entity_key": "mi_sbchapel",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ". The rambling mansion on"
      },
      {
        "text": "State street",
        "entity_key": "statestreet",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", known as the"
      },
      {
        "text": "Park Hotel",
        "entity_key": "parkhotel",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", may have sheltered tourists who read this account."
      },
      {
        "text": "It was the first brick house built in",
        "tropes": [
          9
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "Santa Barbara",
        "tropes": [
          9
        ],
        "entity_key": "ci_sb",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", and was the private residence of",
        "tropes": [
          9
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "Isaac Sparks",
        "tropes": [
          9
        ],
        "entity_key": "isp",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": ", the lessee of",
        "tropes": [
          9
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "the sail boat",
        "tropes": [
          9
        ],
        "entity_key": "sh_peoresnada",
        "entity_type": "ship"
      },
      {
        "text": "from which, in 1835,",
        "tropes": [
          9
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "the woman",
        "tropes": [
          9
        ],
        "entity_key": "lw",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "jumped overboard.",
        "tropes": [
          9
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "\""
      },
      {
        "text": "Burton's Mound",
        "entity_key": "ci_burtons",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ",\" a picturesque knoll, threaded by rows of olive trees, belongs to"
      },
      {
        "text": "Lewis L. Burton",
        "entity_key": "lbu",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": ", another lessee of the"
      },
      {
        "text": "Peor es Nada",
        "entity_key": "sh_peoresnada",
        "entity_type": "ship"
      },
      {
        "text": ". A"
      },
      {
        "text": "lady in San Francisco",
        "entity_key": "woman5",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "has some of the islander's needles."
      },
      {
        "text": "Nidiver",
        "entity_key": "gni",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "and"
      },
      {
        "text": "[B]rown",
        "entity_key": "cdi",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "retain her curious water-tight baskets."
      },
      {
        "text": "The Mission Fathers",
        "entity_keys": [
          "jru",
          "aji",
          "sanchez",
          "misfats"
        ],
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "sent her feather robes to"
      },
      {
        "text": "Rome",
        "entity_key": "ci_rom",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ". They were made of the satiny plumage of the green cormorant, the feathers pointing downward, and so skillfully matched as to seem one continuous sheen of changeful luster."
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "The record of baptism is in the church register. Her grave will be pointed out to any one by"
      },
      {
        "text": "the Franciscan brothers",
        "entity_key": "misfats",
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": "on the hill."
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "(The End.)"
      }
    ]
  ]
}